    "body": "Stopping an IBFT2 validator from mining is somewhat different case to EthHash, and clique.\r\nIn that, in both EthHash and Clique, other miners/signers in the network can pick up the slack, and keep the network moving forwards. IBFT2 is more of a community effort to produce blocks, so, if you stop one validator, its possible you'll stop the entire network.\r\n\r\nWhat is your expected behaviour if you stop an IBFT2 validator? Both at the node, and network level.\r\n\r\nIt's worth noting, that starting/stopping EthHash may be useful due to resource utilisation; however it should be neither Clique nor IBFT2 are resource intensive so the benefits are somewhat reduced. ",
